SocialActionAgent - Class in physicalLayer
An implementation of the Agent abstract class capable of social action, where social action is operationalised as: goal-rational action, where the action taken is considered to be the most likely to achieve a goal; traditional action, where the action taken is comparable to the representative state of the population at the current timestep; random action, where the action taken is completely random. A SocialActionAgent is situated in an environment, that has a two-layered neural network architecture for learning and decision-making.
SocialActionAgent(Cell, int, int) - Constructor for class physicalLayer.SocialActionAgent
Creates an agent capable of social action with an initial location in its environment, empty decision-making layers (random genes) and no allocated targets.
SocialActionAgent(int, int) - Constructor for class physicalLayer.SocialActionAgent
Creates an agent capable of social action, with no initial location in its environment, empty decision-making layers (random genes) and no allocated targets.
SocialActionAgent(int, int, double[][][]) - Constructor for class physicalLayer.SocialActionAgent
Creates an agent capable of social action, with no initial location, populated with given genes in the deliberative layer, an empty reactive layer and no allocated targets.
